The paper proposes a new algorithm for clustering unsupervised data using k-means. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM). The algorithm also deals with large datasets, which suggests it could be relevant to database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the use of k-means for clustering is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV).
